This paper deals with the problem of detecting malicious websites using machine learning algorithms, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on the issue of evasion and counter-evasion between the attacker and defender, which involves adapting the detection model to new attacks, and this is a problem that can be addressed using artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of proactive training as a defense mechanism, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) approach. Finally, the paper deals with cyber attacks, which is a topic in the cyber security (cs.CY) sub-category.
